input_str: Sid Meier’s Civilization games let players rule over a civilization from its foundation in 4,000 B.C. to a theoretical future era powered by fusion technology. Players pick from real historic civilizations and real historic individuals to serve as avatars in their games. These historical figures are typically the most famous leaders in the given civilization’s history. So the American civilization has Washington, Lincoln, FDR, etc. The Roman civilization Julius Caesar, Augustus, Constantine, etc.
